http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Yesudas-musical-nite-organised/article13995393.ece

Admirers of noted playback singer K.J. Yesudas organised a musical nite coinciding with the 76th birthday of the singer.Students of the K.J. Yesudas Samkrithika Seva Samastha led by its founder K. Ratan stole the show, singing evergreen melodies starting with one hailing Lord Maha Ganapati and ending with the song ‘Harivarasanam’ sung in Sabarimala Ayyappa temple every night to put Lord Hariharaputra to sleep.Lyricist Rasa Raju, who penned ‘Andamaina Vennelalona’ song for ‘Assembly Rowdy’ was the chief guest at the musical nite on Sunday which brought to the fore the softer side of Deputy Superintendent of Police G. Srinivasa Rao, who chipped in with a few numbers.